title: Biden and Clinton Try to Narrow Hochul’s Enthusiasm Gap in New York
description: The 11th-hour campaign visits by President Biden and Bill Clinton show that the governor’s race, once a worry-free contest for Democrats, may be up for grabs.
dc:creator: Jesse McKinley

media:content.media:credit: Anna Watts for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Gov. Kathy Hochul was joined in Brooklyn on Saturday by former President Bill Clinton, who accused her Republican opponent, Lee Zeldin, of fearmongering tactics.
